			<link>https://www.brahmakumaris.org#comment-4563</link>
			<description><![CDATA[Rajkumar:  Our soul is made up of a mind, intellect, and sanskaras (impressions/habits).  Since we are thinking beings, conscious thoughts and uncosncious thoughts are always present in the mind.  Some meditations strive to 'have no thoughts'.  Raj Yoga meditation focuses on transforming the kinds of thoughts we have and directing them in the way we want them to go.  However when you concentrate the mind thoughts naturally become slower and peaceful and in deep meditation one can experience 'dead' silence.  When we then become active in the world that experience, and the impact of that silence, remains with us and can change our awareness.  Our awareness affects our atitude, which affects how we see the world, we then act in the world accordingly.]]></description>
